, 
<figureCitation box="[733,801,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[163,1411,190,1552]" captionTargetId="figure-18@15.[151,1435,181,1560]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male genitalia (A–M) and everted endophallus (N–Q) of Anomala spp. A–C, A. linwenhsini Zhao &amp; Zorn, new species, holotype; D–G, A. wutaiensis Zhao &amp; Zorn, new species, holotype; H–J, N–O, A. kanshireiensis Zorn &amp; Zhao, new species, holotype; K–M, P–Q, A. inclinata Zhao &amp; Zorn, new species, holotype. A, D, H, K, dorsal view; B, F, I, L, N, P, right lateral view; E, O, Q, left lateral view; C, G, J, M, ventral view. Sc 1, scale bar for A–M = 2 mm; Sc 2, scale bar for N–Q = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6877289" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6877289/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="180">9A–C</figureCitation>
